This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques for shadow removal. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV. The paper also discusses the use of adversarial learning and cycle-consistency constraints, which are common techniques in generative models and deep learning. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (machine learning), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), and cs.GR (graphics). Finally, the paper includes experiments on various datasets, which suggests that it may also be relevant to cs.MM (multimedia).
